With Hanukkah fast approaching, here are three new Jewish cookbooks that would make great gifts this year! 

The Modern Table: Kosher Recipes for Everyday Gatherings by Kim Kushner (Figure 1)
This stunning book featuring fresh ingredients, bright flavours and simple techniques has redefined kosher cuisine. And you don’t have to be kosher to love it – I love it.
 
Modern Jewish Comfort Food: 100 Fresh Recipes For Classic Dishes from Kugel to Kreplach by Shannon Sarna (WW Norton)
From the founding editor of the very popular food blog The Nosher, this new cookbook offers traditional and modern takes on many favourite Jewish foods.
 
Koshersoul: The Faith and Food Journey of an African American Jew by Michael Twitty (HarperCollins)
From the author of The Cooking Gene, a deep and meaningful combination of memoir, history, recipes and stories that could change the way you look at food and faith.
 
